<h2 id="useradd">useradd</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>-c</strong>: add a comment (typically used for the userâ€™s full name)</li>
  <li><strong>-d</strong>: specify home directory (but this doesnâ€™t necessarily create it)</li>
  <li><strong>-m</strong>: create home diretory</li>
  <li><strong>-r</strong>: system account (for things like Apache where itâ€™s best to run under a user acct)</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="usermod">usermod</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>-a</strong>: append; adds user to groups (only use with -G option)</li>
  <li><strong>-c</strong>: overwrite current comment</li>
  <li><strong>-d</strong>: specify new home direcctory</li>
  <li><strong>-G</strong>: a list of groups that the user is a member of (overwrites the list unless used with -a)</li>
  <li><strong>-L</strong>: lock password (this wonâ€™t block SSH with a key)</li>
  <li><strong>-m</strong>: move home (move userâ€™s home to a new location)</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="groupadd">groupadd</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>-r</strong>: system</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="groupmod">groupmod</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>-n</strong>: new name for the group</li>
</ul>
